race.comment: MIC DROP (10) has made a seamless start for her new yard, stringing together two strong wins over this track and trip. She rises in grade but gets weight relief and is drawn to advantage. No reason she can't keep the ball rolling. DANCING STORM (4) has been solid without quite threatening in his past two, but he gets weight relief here and maps to slot in beautifully again with Toeroek staying aboard. Very capable of featuring. THE STALKER (5) showed his trademark speed here last week when leading throughout. He draws well again and will take catching if left alone. CLARENCE (9) is knocking on the door and gets his chance on the quick back-up, dropping nicely in the weights. He should settle handy and be right there when it matters. SALSA FELLOW (6) has been good in both Victorian runs this prep, is peaking now and has to be included.
